1
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:14,700
<i>This tumor could be the root
cause of your symptoms.</i>

2
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:16,733
<i> The location is critical.</i>

3
00:00:16,867 --> 00:00:18,333
<i> Do I need surgery?</i>

4
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:20,667
<i>I want to seek a second opinion.</i>

5
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> Okay.</i>

6
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:24,667
<i>My cousin is one of the top
neurologists in Davao.</i>

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,700
<i>Do you want us to go home now
so you can rest?</i>

8
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:28,100
<i> I don't want to go home yet.</i>

9
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:31,067
<i> Wow, what a coincidence.</i>

10
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,567
<i>Felma seems to be doing well,
Manuel.</i>

11
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:34,767
<i> Look.</i>

12
00:00:34,933 --> 00:00:37,933
<i>Mind if we share a table?
Just like a double date?</i>

13
00:00:38,067 --> 00:00:39,067
No!

14
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:08,333
So...

15
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:13,700
I heard you went in
for a checkup?

16
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,467
Why?

17
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:19,000
Are you sick?

18
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:23,733
Are you dying or something?

19
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:32,467
Don't tell me...

20
00:01:33,867 --> 00:01:35,167
you really are sick?

21
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,267
Is it cancer?

22
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:42,800
Stage 4.

23
00:01:44,133 --> 00:01:45,100
Really?

24
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,567
I mean,

25
00:01:49,767 --> 00:01:51,433
I'm sorry to hear that.

26
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:59,167
Hazel.

27
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:01,800
You're like one of those stupid
netizens.

28
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:04,267
You believe fake news
so quickly.

29
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,300
I'm not sick.

30
00:02:08,367 --> 00:02:10,600
And I'm not dying.

31
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:15,600
So don't be so excited.

32
00:02:19,567 --> 00:02:21,100
You're funny, aren't you?

33
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:22,700
You already have everything.

34
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:23,900
You have Manuel.

35
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:26,567
And yet, you still lose to me.

36
00:02:27,733 --> 00:02:30,733
What do you mean I lost?
How exactly did I lose to you?

37
00:02:30,867 --> 00:02:32,033
Of course.

38
00:02:34,767 --> 00:02:37,133
You've proven it just now.

39
00:02:37,267 --> 00:02:40,767
You know that it's me
that Manuel loves.

40
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:45,767
That's why you got excited
when you heard I'm dying.

41
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:49,767
Because that's the only way
for you to win.

42
00:02:51,033 --> 00:02:57,467
You'll have hope that Manuel
might love you once I'm gone.

43
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:18,900
<i>I hope this letter reaches
the right hands.</i>

44
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:22,400
<i>Hazel Cruz paid me to falsely
accuse Coleen Cruz</i>

45
00:03:22,567 --> 00:03:25,367
<i>of the death of her daughter,
Jessica Cruz.</i>

46
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:27,600
<i>Later, she forced me
to take it all back.</i>

47
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:29,467
<i> Now she's threatening me.</i>

48
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,500
<i> Telling me to keep quiet.</i>

49
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:34,533
<i> My life is in danger in here.</i>

50
00:03:34,667 --> 00:03:37,600
<i>I don't know which of the people
around me is working for her.</i>

51
00:03:37,733 --> 00:03:41,000
<i>But I'm even more afraid
for my wife and children.</i>

52
00:03:41,133 --> 00:03:43,867
<i>God knows what Hazel could do
to them.</i>

53
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:45,767
That's it.

54
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,367
That's a confession, bro.

55
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,600
Uncle Manuel and Aunt Felma
were right about it.

56
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:53,367
You really are evil, Hazel.

57
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,633
Coleen almost went to jail
because of you.

58
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:01,800
Monsters!

59
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:04,767
They're evil! Go, Jeff.
Report it.

60
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,267
<i> Not that fast, Dad.</i>

61
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,967
Let's make a concrete plan
first.

62
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:10,300
Hazel's people might catch on.

63
00:04:10,433 --> 00:04:14,967
Let's secure Timo's wife
and children first.

64
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:16,033
They have to be safe.

65
00:04:16,167 --> 00:04:17,633
Okay, okay.

66
00:04:17,767 --> 00:04:19,567
I'll get Diana's number.

67
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:20,733
<i> Okay, Dad.</i>

68
00:04:20,867 --> 00:04:21,967
Be safe.

69
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:25,167
And make sure Hazel doesn't
find out that you know.

70
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,200
<i> Okay, Jeff.</i>

71
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,333
Hazel's coming.
I'll call you again.

72
00:04:31,967 --> 00:04:32,900
There you are.

73
00:04:33,033 --> 00:04:35,633
I had a takeout,
so we don't have to cook later.

74
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:40,967
Do you want anything else?

75
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,233
Do you want a dessert?

76
00:04:42,367 --> 00:04:44,000
- No, I'm okay.
- Should I get takeout, too?

77
00:04:44,133 --> 00:04:45,933
- No, it's okay. Yes.
- Sure?

78
00:04:46,067 --> 00:04:48,700
Are you sure?
Their cake is good.

79
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:50,467
I'm all good.

80
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,633
Okay, let's go.

81
00:05:06,567 --> 00:05:10,933
You were already in bed
before I went out, right?

82
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:14,067
I just went to pee, Hazel.

83
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:27,300
How did you get into
your wheelchair?

84
00:05:29,367 --> 00:05:32,767
It's just my leg
that's paralyzed.

85
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:35,867
I crawled. I used my hands.

86
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,367
You didn't call me?

87
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:42,967
Sorry.
I was embarrassed to bother you.

88
00:05:44,167 --> 00:05:48,667
Manuel, next time, call me.

89
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,233
How many times
do I have to say it?

90
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:51,800
I want to take care of you.

91
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:54,400
Okay. Next time, I'll call you.

92
00:05:59,867 --> 00:06:02,800
Wow. That's surprising.
You didn't argue with me?

93
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,167
No.

94
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,400
I'm just tired of saying no
to you.

95
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:10,067
It's exhausting.
We always end up fighting.

96
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,367
Good.

97
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:15,367
At least you finally realized
it.

98
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,300
Because I won't stop anyway.

99
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,067
All right.
I'll just take a shower.

100
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:21,967
Alice and I still have somewhere
to go.

101
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:49,867
Her birthday.

102
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:57,633
Jessica's birthday.

103
00:07:02,633 --> 00:07:04,033
Anniversary.

104
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:05,800
Our anniversary.

105
00:07:15,433 --> 00:07:16,500
Manuel?

106
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:22,333
Is someone calling me?

107
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:23,967
Alice is calling.

108
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:31,100
Hello, Alice.

109
00:07:32,167 --> 00:07:34,500
Come on, I was just
about to take a shower.

110
00:07:34,633 --> 00:07:35,633
I'll see you in a while.

111
00:07:36,033 --> 00:07:37,033
<i> What?</i>

112
00:07:37,167 --> 00:07:40,100
You asked me to call
you after five minutes.

113
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:41,367
Wait.

114
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,333
Don't tell me you're using me
as an alibi,

115
00:07:43,467 --> 00:07:45,700
so Manuel will think
we're meeting?

116
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:46,867
Yes, Alice.

117
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,800
What are you up to now?

118
00:07:48,967 --> 00:07:50,500
Who are you meeting?

119
00:07:50,633 --> 00:07:51,767
Okay. I'll see you
in 30 minutes.

120
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:52,800
Bye.

121
00:07:56,567 --> 00:07:57,700
Oh, Alice.

122
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:19,667
Diana's number.

123
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:20,967
Diana.

124
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:23,000
Diana.

125
00:08:26,267 --> 00:08:27,233
Diana.

126
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:40,467
Mom, thank God,
it's just a migraine

127
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,467
that caused your headache.

128
00:08:44,533 --> 00:08:46,567
We were really worried
it might be something serious.

129
00:08:48,467 --> 00:08:49,400
Thank you, Lord.

130
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:54,000
Ma'am, are you sure
that's all it is?

131
00:08:55,133 --> 00:08:56,133
Oh, please, Didang.

132
00:08:56,267 --> 00:08:57,033
Here you go again.

133
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:58,900
Didang's starting again.

134
00:09:00,167 --> 00:09:02,500
You two, honestly.

135
00:09:02,633 --> 00:09:04,467
Ma'am, I'm serious.

136
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:06,333
If the symptoms permit...

137
00:09:06,467 --> 00:09:09,200
Didang, persist.

138
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:11,733
Persist.

139
00:09:11,867 --> 00:09:12,767
Oh, dear.

140
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:14,067
You two...

141
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,600
no matter how I said it,
you still understood me, right?

142
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:21,067
I really am serious, Ma'am.

143
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:24,533
If your headache acts up again,

144
00:09:24,667 --> 00:09:25,800
come on.

145
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:29,233
Let's have you cleansed
by my relatives in Aklan.

146
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,600
What? Aklan?

147
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:33,700
That's so far, Didang.

148
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:34,833
Come on.

149
00:09:34,967 --> 00:09:36,733
We'll do it online.

150
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:38,367
There are online wakes now.

151
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:39,767
Of course,
there's online cleansing.

152
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,700
The things you come up with.

153
00:09:45,433 --> 00:09:47,133
Mom?

154
00:09:47,267 --> 00:09:49,333
I'm getting sleepy.

155
00:09:51,133 --> 00:09:52,167
Me too, Mom.

156
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:55,833
I feel really tired.
I got tired because of Didang.

157
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:57,867
All right, you two go ahead.

158
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
I'll rest in a bit, too.

159
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:03,067
Love you, Mom.

160
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,000
I love you too, sweetie.

161
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:05,700
Good night, Mom.

162
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:09,433
Come on, baby sister.

163
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:10,567
Let's go.

164
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:12,900
Ma'am, I'll make sure these two
really go to sleep.

165
00:10:13,033 --> 00:10:14,033
We are sleeping!

166
00:10:14,167 --> 00:10:15,000
Didang, stop it.

167
00:10:15,133 --> 00:10:15,600
You'll just end up holding
your phones.

168
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:17,233
I know you two.

169
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:28,100
It's perfect timing
that you called us in, Miss H.

170
00:10:28,233 --> 00:10:30,433
We don't have any side gigs
right now.

171
00:10:30,567 --> 00:10:32,300
Do you have something
for us to do?

172
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,500
Obviously.

173
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:37,500
That's why I called you.

174
00:10:37,633 --> 00:10:39,667
Do you think I just want to bond
with you?

175
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,700
Of course not.

176
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:43,300
I have a job for you.

177
00:10:43,433 --> 00:10:44,800
What is it, Miss H?

178
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:01,433
Dad.

179
00:11:02,567 --> 00:11:03,433
Hello, Jeff.

180
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:06,700
I already sent you Diana's
number.

181
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,333
<i>You handle it from here,
all right?</i>

182
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:09,333
Okay, Dad.

183
00:11:09,467 --> 00:11:10,767
<i> Thanks.</i>

184
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:12,700
Is your mother there?

185
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:13,900
Just a moment.

186
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:21,333
Mom?

187
00:11:22,667 --> 00:11:23,967
It's Dad.

188
00:11:34,633 --> 00:11:35,467
Manuel?

189
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:37,567
Hello, Felma.

190
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:38,467
You know,

191
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:42,933
I really wanted
to hug you earlier.

192
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,867
I miss you so much.

193
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,333
I miss you too, Manuel.

194
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:48,867
But...

195
00:11:50,267 --> 00:11:52,600
we're not allowed
to miss each other.

196
00:11:52,733 --> 00:11:54,067
Just a little more time, Felma.

197
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,400
A little more time.

198
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:56,733
For what?

199
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:58,133
<i> Never mind.</i>

200
00:11:58,267 --> 00:12:00,200
I'll tell you later.

201
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:03,800
So, how was your checkup?

202
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,333
Yeah.

203
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:12,733
I'm fine.

204
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:14,667
<i> Are you sure?</i>

205
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:17,433
Felma, I don't want you
to get sick while I'm far away.

206
00:12:17,567 --> 00:12:19,333
<i> I know.</i>

207
00:12:19,467 --> 00:12:20,633
I'm strong.

208
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,600
I can't get sick.

209
00:12:23,733 --> 00:12:25,100
<i> I can't.</i>

210
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:26,600
Yes, Felma.

211
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:29,167
You really can't get sick.

212
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:32,300
You can only get sick
if I'm right beside you.

213
00:12:32,433 --> 00:12:34,400
Because I want to be the one
to take care of you.

214
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:35,967
Just me. No one else.

215
00:13:03,633 --> 00:13:05,033
Just a little more time, Felma.

216
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:08,667
I'm coming home to you soon.

217
00:13:10,533 --> 00:13:12,367
Our family will finally
be whole.

218
00:13:13,533 --> 00:13:15,367
No one will be able
to separate us.

219
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:20,867
Nothing will break us apart.

220
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,767
Except death.

221
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:33,000
I'm scared.

222
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,333
I'm afraid you'll take me.

223
00:13:39,867 --> 00:13:41,733
Please help me.

224
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,633
Please help me.

225
00:13:45,767 --> 00:13:48,800
I can't do this.

226
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:50,800
<i> And this one concerns us.</i>

227
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:53,533
<i> What is it, Doctor?</i>

228
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:54,900
<i> A tumor.</i>

229
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:56,533
<i> I want...</i>

230
00:13:56,667 --> 00:13:58,533
<i> I want a second opinion.</i>

231
00:13:58,667 --> 00:13:59,867
<i> Okay.</i>

232
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,667
<i> I heard you had a checkup.</i>

233
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,900
<i> Are you dying or something?</i>

234
00:14:04,033 --> 00:14:05,567
<i> Mom, thank God,</i>

235
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:08,700
<i>it's just a migraine causing
your headaches.</i>

236
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:11,200
<i>We thought it was
something else.</i>

237
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:13,633
<i> Is that really all it is?</i>

238
00:14:13,767 --> 00:14:16,833
<i>You're only allowed to get
sick if I'm beside you.</i>

239
00:14:16,967 --> 00:14:17,933
Please, no.

240
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:18,800
<i>I want to be the one
who takes care of you.</i>

241
00:14:18,933 --> 00:14:20,167
<i> Just me. No one else.</i>

242
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:24,333
Please don't let
my fear come true.

243
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:29,000
My children still need me.

244
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:33,533
I can't leave them.

245
00:14:35,933 --> 00:14:37,767
My God, they need me.

246
00:14:40,267 --> 00:14:43,167
They need me,
that's why I'm begging you.

247
00:14:44,367 --> 00:14:45,500
I don't want this.

248
00:14:48,633 --> 00:14:50,500
Please don't take me.

249
00:14:52,233 --> 00:14:56,567
Please don't take me.

250
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:59,267
Please don't take me.

251
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:02,100
- Not yet.
- Ma'am?

252
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:05,600
- Not yet.
- Ma'am...

253
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:06,933
Did I hear you right?

254
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:11,867
"Don't take me"?

255
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,000
Why, Ma'am?

256
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:16,067
Why are you begging
God like that?

257
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:19,400
What is the real
result of your test?

258
00:15:19,533 --> 00:15:20,433
Didang...

259
00:15:23,067 --> 00:15:25,467
Didang, I have a
tumor in my brain.

260
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:27,400
What?

261
00:15:27,533 --> 00:15:29,533
I have a brain tumor.

262
00:15:42,133 --> 00:15:43,700
Is it cancer, Ma'am?

263
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:48,600
I don't know.

264
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:49,700
I don't know.

265
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:53,100
Ma'am, what did your doctor say?

266
00:15:55,633 --> 00:15:57,033
They want to...

267
00:15:57,167 --> 00:15:58,433
they want to operate.

268
00:15:58,567 --> 00:15:59,533
They want to remove it.

269
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,733
Then why don't we do it?

270
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:04,300
Maybe that's how
you'll get better.

271
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:07,500
I'm scared, Didang.

272
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,500
What are you scared of, Ma'am?

273
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:15,100
That I won't wake up.

274
00:16:19,533 --> 00:16:23,600
I can't leave my children.

275
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:25,400
I don't want to, Didang.

276
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:31,000
I know they're grown-ups now,

277
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:38,233
but I haven't prepared them
for a life without me.

278
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:41,867
They're not ready.

279
00:16:45,433 --> 00:16:46,833
They don't have
a father anymore.

280
00:16:48,233 --> 00:16:49,133
I don't want...

281
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:52,567
I don't want them to
lose their mother, too.

282
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:56,900
Ma'am, don't talk like that.

283
00:16:57,033 --> 00:16:59,733
Ma'am, you're not going to die.

284
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:04,033
We don't know that, Didang.

285
00:17:04,167 --> 00:17:06,633
We don't know that.

286
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:09,767
Be brave, Ma'am.

287
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:11,533
Be strong.

288
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:17,033
If you ever feel weak...

289
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,467
or if fear starts
to consume you,

290
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:22,500
I'm right here.

291
00:17:22,633 --> 00:17:24,633
I'll be your strength.

292
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:28,867
I'll be the one you lean on.

293
00:17:32,267 --> 00:17:35,500
I will be strong for you, Ma'am.

294
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:39,933
Thank you, Didang.

295
00:17:40,067 --> 00:17:41,933
I just have one request.

296
00:17:42,067 --> 00:17:43,667
What is it, Ma'am?

297
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:46,533
Don't tell the children.

298
00:17:46,667 --> 00:17:50,233
Only you and Noah
know about this.

299
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:52,267
No, Ma'am.

300
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:54,600
I won't tell anyone.

301
00:17:54,733 --> 00:17:57,533
I know I'm usually a gossip,

302
00:17:57,667 --> 00:18:02,667
but when it's this serious,
I won't let a word slip.

303
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:05,300
No one will know.

304
00:18:05,433 --> 00:18:06,767
I promise.

305
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:10,067
I will keep this secret, Ma'am.

306
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,133
Ma'am!

307
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:31,133
Attorney Salazar's been
calling you, Hazel.

308
00:18:31,267 --> 00:18:32,533
You're not answering.

309
00:18:32,667 --> 00:18:34,833
Timo got beaten up in jail.

310
00:18:37,467 --> 00:18:39,200
Don't tell me you had
something to do with it?

311
00:18:42,633 --> 00:18:44,433
Keep your voice down.

312
00:18:44,567 --> 00:18:46,700
Manuel might hear you.

313
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:48,133
I just wanted him
to learn his lesson.

314
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,500
What?

315
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:51,533
Why?

316
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:54,767
Just to remind him that
I'm still in business.

317
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:58,667
One more word from him,
and that won't be all he gets.

318
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:01,467
My god, Hazel.

319
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,900
What if that just
makes him talk more?

320
00:19:04,033 --> 00:19:05,500
Let him try.

321
00:19:05,633 --> 00:19:07,133
His wife and kids
are dead if he does.

322
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:08,267
And his mother, too.

323
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,900
You're scaring me.

324
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:15,700
You already sound
like a criminal.

325
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,233
Aren't you afraid you'll
get caught for all this?

326
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:22,233
They should be afraid of me.

327
00:19:22,367 --> 00:19:23,733
So just relax.

328
00:19:23,867 --> 00:19:24,867
Don't worry.

329
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:25,833
I won't get caught.

330
00:19:25,967 --> 00:19:27,433
<i> That's what you think, Hazel.</i>

331
00:19:34,533 --> 00:19:36,233
How long have you been there?

332
00:19:36,367 --> 00:19:37,900
I just got here.

333
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:40,433
Is there a problem?

334
00:19:42,067 --> 00:19:42,800
Nothing.

335
00:19:44,033 --> 00:19:46,233
It's just that...

336
00:19:46,367 --> 00:19:50,833
Alice was telling me
about this...

337
00:19:50,967 --> 00:19:53,600
apparently, there's a ghost
at Southcrest Hospital.

338
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:54,700
What is it again?

339
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,000
Yeah, Manuel.

340
00:19:56,133 --> 00:19:57,233
A crying child.

341
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:01,100
That is creepy.

342
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:03,000
Hazel, I made breakfast.

343
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:05,233
Let's eat.

344
00:20:05,367 --> 00:20:06,600
Alice.

345
00:20:06,733 --> 00:20:07,467
Really?

346
00:20:10,567 --> 00:20:11,367
Okay.

347
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:18,133
You're not going to
work again, Jeff?

348
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,267
Joel and I have
somewhere to go.

349
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,433
What is it with all
these errands of yours?

350
00:20:25,567 --> 00:20:26,800
Why?

351
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:28,533
All right, I'm leaving. Bye.

352
00:20:28,667 --> 00:20:30,000
- Didang, this is okay.
- Yes.

353
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:30,867
Take care, okay?

354
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:31,900
I've got this.

355
00:20:32,033 --> 00:20:32,600
Mom, bye.

356
00:20:36,133 --> 00:20:37,533
Why is he in such a hurry?

357
00:20:37,667 --> 00:20:38,733
Where is he going?

358
00:20:38,867 --> 00:20:40,500
I don't know, Mom.

359
00:20:40,633 --> 00:20:43,433
He and Joel are always
going somewhere.

360
00:20:43,567 --> 00:20:45,767
They talk in secret.

361
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:47,367
I keep catching them.

362
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:50,300
And it looks like
Dad's involved, too.

363
00:20:50,433 --> 00:20:50,967
Come on!

364
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:52,133
Let's go together.

365
00:20:52,267 --> 00:20:52,833
Wait, Ma'am.

366
00:20:52,967 --> 00:20:54,367
You're not having breakfast?

367
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,567
No, I won't.

368
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:56,767
I'll eat at the office later.

369
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,400
I'm not really hungry.

370
00:20:58,533 --> 00:21:00,333
No, no, no, Ma'am.

371
00:21:00,467 --> 00:21:02,100
You have to eat.

372
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:04,600
You're taking your medicine
and vitamins.

373
00:21:04,733 --> 00:21:06,467
What if it gets bigger?

374
00:21:14,300 --> 00:21:16,500
What will get bigger, Didang?

375
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:18,200
I mean...

376
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:19,233
worse.

377
00:21:19,367 --> 00:21:21,967
Your migraine might
get worse, Ma'am.

378
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:22,733
Right?

379
00:21:22,867 --> 00:21:23,733
It could get worse.

380
00:21:23,867 --> 00:21:25,400
I don't want that to get worse.

381
00:21:25,533 --> 00:21:28,133
Thanks for the reminder, Didang.

382
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:32,700
Andrea, let's go to the car.

383
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:34,633
I'll wait for you, okay?

384
00:21:34,767 --> 00:21:35,700
I'm just going to
brush my teeth, Mom.

385
00:21:35,833 --> 00:21:36,967
Just a minute.

386
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:38,733
She really didn't eat breakfast.

387
00:21:40,533 --> 00:21:41,400
Take care!

388
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:44,200
Didang?

389
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:45,233
Oh, dear.

390
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,700
I'll take care of
cleaning up here, okay?

391
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:49,167
I'll just check on the laundry.

392
00:22:20,167 --> 00:22:24,633
My child, all I want is for you
to be at peace.

393
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:29,800
But forgive me for what I have
to do with your mom.

394
00:22:29,933 --> 00:22:33,467
I can't grant your wish for us
to be together again,

395
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:35,700
if it's true.

396
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:38,533
Because of all her lies...

397
00:22:40,867 --> 00:22:42,067
I'll have her put in jail.

398
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:58,700
Felma, when I get back,
I'll be bringing Emil with me.

399
00:22:58,833 --> 00:22:59,800
Who is he, Sir?

400
00:22:59,933 --> 00:23:00,833
My cousin.

401
00:23:00,967 --> 00:23:01,800
He's a neurologist.

402
00:23:01,933 --> 00:23:03,300
Book me a ticket.

403
00:23:03,433 --> 00:23:05,567
I'm going with you
to Davao later.

404
00:23:07,433 --> 00:23:09,100
Let go of me!

405
00:23:09,233 --> 00:23:10,333
No one move!

406
00:23:10,467 --> 00:23:13,233
Hey!

407
00:23:13,367 --> 00:23:17,200
We were instructed to
scare Diana Malabanan.

408
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:19,933
We're here for Mrs. Hazel Cruz.

409
00:23:20,067 --> 00:23:21,633
What do you need from my wife?

410
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,933
We'd like to invite her
to the station.
